Differnce between Error and Exception
Definition

Error is used in situations when there is nothing a programmer can do about an error
Exception
Exception is used when a programmer can handle the exception.

#)Both come from the parent class Throwable, but:

Throwable
 ├── Exception   → can be handled
 we can handle using try and catch.

 └── Error       → cannot be handled
 we cannot handle using try and catch.
 Usually caused by the JVM or system environment


 #)Exception
 IOException, SQLException, NullPointerException, ArithmeticException


 #)Error 
 OutOfMemoryError, StackOverflowError, VirtualMachineError